The separation of our CCOP business segment on August 1, 2015 required significant time and attention from management and resulted in increased operating expenses, some of which may continue to be incurred in the near term. This may prevent us from fully achieving the anticipated benefits of the separation. Additionally, uncertainty related to the separation may lead customers and other parties to terminate or attempt to negotiate changes in existing business relationships. These disruptions could have a material and adverse effect on our businesses, financial condition, results of operations, and prospects.
 
