We recently announced the departure of Thomas Waechter, who was our President and Chief Executive Officer since January, 2009. Richard Belluzzo, Chairman of our Board, has agreed to serve as Interim President and Chief Executive Officer while we conduct a search for a replacement. Additionally, Rex Jackson, our Chief Financial Officer since January 2012, previously announced he will depart September 30, 2015. Amar Maletira will join the Company as Chief Financial Officer on September 9, 2015. Furthermore, in connection with the separation of the Lumentum business, we eliminated a number of other executive roles in our business and corporate functions during fiscal 2015. The extent of our management changes could adversely impact our results of operations and our customer relationships and may make recruiting for future management positions more difficult. If we are unable to attract and retain qualified executives and employees, or to successfully integrate any newly-hired personnel within our organization, we may be unable to achieve our operating objectives, which could negatively impact our financial performance and results of operations.
